# Put this folder to the login node of the HPC cluster that you want to monitor
# Modify the HPC1.config file according to your HPC cluster setup
# You can name HPC1.config to the name of your cluster such as my_cluster.config. "my_cluster" section will be displayed on the monitoing tool as the cluster name.

# COLLECTING CLUSTER DATA
# make sure the hosting server is set up first and working.
# run ./collect_data/data_collect.sh on the login node 'once'. This will generate cluster infrastructure data.
